</taxonomicName>
sp. nov.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="151" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
The new genus-group name is a combination of the Ancient Greek 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<normalizedToken originalValue="orthós">orthos</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
(
<normalizedToken originalValue="ο’ρθός">ο'ρθός</normalizedToken>
, meaning, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“upright”">&quot;upright&quot;</normalizedToken>
or 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“erect”">&quot;erect&quot;</normalizedToken>
, and geometrically &quot;right angle&quot;), and the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Rohwer, 1915" authorityName="Rohwer" authorityYear="1915" class="Insecta" family="Anaxyelidae" genus="Syntexis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Syntexis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Syntexis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(itself from Ancient Greek 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<normalizedToken originalValue="súntēxis">suntēxis</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
(σύντηξις, meaning, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“colliquescence”">&quot;colliquescence&quot;</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“emaciating”">&quot;emaciating&quot;</normalizedToken>
, or &quot;wasting away&quot;)), type genus of the subfamily 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benson" authorityYear="1935" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Syntexinae">Syntexinae</taxonomicName>
. Gender feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="151" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Female</emphasis>
: Antenna with 16 flagellomeres, scape almost 3
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as width and twice as long as flagellomere I, flagellomere I nearly 1.5
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as flagellomere II. Forewing with pterostigma not enlarged, uniformly sclerotized and of normal width; 1Rs shorter than 1M; cell 1mcu length to width ratio slightly more than 2; 1r-rs and 2rs-m absent; 1Cu obviously shorter than 2Cu; 3Cu shorter than 4Cu; 2m-cu 1.5
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
shorter than 1m-cu in forewing; 3rs-m 2
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
shorter than 4M. Hind wing with abscissa 2M+Cu; 1M shorter than 2M; m-cu absent, cell r closed. Mesotibia with two apical spurs. Male: Unknown. Immatures: Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="151" type="included species">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Included species.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. Gao, Engel, Shih, &amp; T. Gao" authorityYear="2021" family="Anaxyelidae" genus="Orthosyntexis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Orthosyntexis elegans" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Orthosyntexis elegans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. and 
<taxonomicName genus="O." lsidName="O. thanti" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="thanti">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">O. thanti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="151" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. Gao, Engel, Shih, &amp; T. Gao" authorityYear="2021" family="Anaxyelidae" genus="Orthosyntexis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Orthosyntexis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Orthosyntexis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be differentiated from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kopylov" authorityYear="2019" class="Insecta" family="Anaxyelidae" genus="Curiosyntexis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Curiosyntexis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Curiosyntexis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in which the forewing pterostigma is desclerotized and 1r-rs is partly reduced (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4603.2.7" author="Kopylov, DS" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="341 - 353" refId="B10" refString="Kopylov, DS, 2019. New anaxyelids (Hymenoptera: Anaxyelidae) from the Cretaceous of Asia. Zootaxa 4603: 341 - 353, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4603.2.7" title="New anaxyelids (Hymenoptera: Anaxyelidae) from the Cretaceous of Asia." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4603.2.7" volume="4603" year="2019">Kopylov 2019</bibRefCitation>
), and from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kopylov" authorityYear="2019" class="Insecta" family="Anaxyelidae" genus="Dolichosyntexis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dolichosyntexis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dolichosyntexis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which has an enlarged pterostigma and forewing 1Cu not obviously shorter than 2Cu (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4603.2.7" author="Kopylov, DS" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="341 - 353" refId="B10" refString="Kopylov, DS, 2019. New anaxyelids (Hymenoptera: Anaxyelidae) from the Cretaceous of Asia. Zootaxa 4603: 341 - 353, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4603.2.7" title="New anaxyelids (Hymenoptera: Anaxyelidae) from the Cretaceous of Asia." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4603.2.7" volume="4603" year="2019">Kopylov 2019</bibRefCitation>
). The new genus can be separated from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kopylov" authorityYear="2019" class="Insecta" family="Anaxyelidae" genus="Parasyntexis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Parasyntexis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Parasyntexis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="latter’s">latter's</normalizedToken>
narrower pterostigma, narrower than the length of 2r-rs, and 1M longer than 2M in the hind wing (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4603.2.7" author="Kopylov, DS" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="341 - 353" refId="B10" refString="Kopylov, DS, 2019. New anaxyelids (Hymenoptera: Anaxyelidae) from the Cretaceous of Asia. Zootaxa 4603: 341 - 353, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4603.2.7" title="New anaxyelids (Hymenoptera: Anaxyelidae) from the Cretaceous of Asia." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4603.2.7" volume="4603" year="2019">Kopylov 2019</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. Gao, Engel, Shih, &amp; T. Gao" authorityYear="2021" family="Anaxyelidae" genus="Orthosyntexis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Orthosyntexis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Orthosyntexis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Anaxyelidae" genus="Sclerosyntexis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sclerosyntexis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Sclerosyntexis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="latter’s">latter's</normalizedToken>
elongate scape, which is 3
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide, and the open cell r in the hind wing (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.cretres.2020.104372" author="Wang, YM" journalOrPublisher="Historical Biology" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" refId="B36" refString="Wang, YM, Wang, M, Rasnitsyn, AP, Shih, CK, Ren, D, Kopylov, DS, Gao, TP, 2020. A new anaxyelid sawfly (Insecta, Hymenoptera, Siricoidea) in mid-Cretaceous Myanmar amber. Cretaceous Research 109: 104372. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.cretres.2020.104372" title="A new anaxyelid sawfly (Insecta, Hymenoptera, Siricoidea) in mid-Cretaceous Myanmar amber. Cretaceous Research 109: 104372." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.cretres.2020.104372" year="2020">Wang et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. Gao, Engel, Shih, &amp; T. Gao" authorityYear="2021" family="Anaxyelidae" genus="Orthosyntexis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Orthosyntexis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Orthosyntexis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the extant genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Rohwer, 1915" authorityName="Rohwer" authorityYear="1915" class="Insecta" family="Anaxyelidae" genus="Syntexis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Syntexis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Syntexis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which has 3Cu longer than 4Cu and 2m-cu 1.5
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than 1m-cu in the forewing (
<bibRefCitation author="Rohwer, SA" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="114 - 117" refId="B24" refString="Rohwer, SA, 1915. A remarkable new genus of Cephidae. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington 17: 114 - 117" title="A remarkable new genus of Cephidae." volume="17" year="1915">Rohwer 1915</bibRefCitation>
), and from 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Anaxyelidae" genus="Daosyntexis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Daosyntexis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Daosyntexis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 1Rs 3
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
being longer than 1M and 3rs-m 2
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than 4M in the forewing (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/03115518.2019.1697753" author="Kopylov, DS" journalOrPublisher="Alcheringa: An Australasian Journal of Palaeontology" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="104 - 114" refId="B11" refString="Kopylov, DS, Rasnitsyn, AP, Zhang, HC, Zhang, Q, 2020. Anaxyelidae of Daohugou: oldest occurrences of the relict family in the fossil record. Part1: Daosyntexis and Brachysyntexis. Alcheringa: An Australasian Journal of Palaeontology 44: 104 - 114, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/03115518.2019.1697753" title="Anaxyelidae of Daohugou: oldest occurrences of the relict family in the fossil record. Part 1: Daosyntexis and Brachysyntexis." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/03115518.2019.1697753" volume="44" year="2020">Kopylov et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
). The new genus differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rasnitsyn &amp; Martinez-Delclos" authorityYear="2000" class="Insecta" family="Anaxyelidae" genus="Cretosyntexis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cretosyntexis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Cretosyntexis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 2r-rs meeting the pterostigma beyond midlength and Rs+M longer than 2M (
<bibRefCitation author="Rasnitsyn, AP" journalOrPublisher="Acta Geologica Hispanica" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="65 - 95" refId="B22" refString="Rasnitsyn, AP, Martinez-Delclos, X, 2000. Wasps (Insecta: Vespida = Hymenoptera) from the Early Cretaceous of Spain. Acta Geologica Hispanica 35: 65 - 95" title="Wasps (Insecta: Vespida = Hymenoptera) from the Early Cretaceous of Spain." volume="35" year="2000">
Rasnitsyn and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Martínez-Delclòs">Martinez-Delclos</normalizedToken>
2000
</bibRefCitation>
), and from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rasnitsyn" authorityYear="1990" class="Insecta" family="Anaxyelidae" genus="Eosyntexis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eosyntexis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Eosyntexis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in which 1RS is not shorter than 1M (
<bibRefCitation author="Rasnitsyn, AP" journalOrPublisher="Acta Geologica Hispanica" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="65 - 95" refId="B22" refString="Rasnitsyn, AP, Martinez-Delclos, X, 2000. Wasps (Insecta: Vespida = Hymenoptera) from the Early Cretaceous of Spain. Acta Geologica Hispanica 35: 65 - 95" title="Wasps (Insecta: Vespida = Hymenoptera) from the Early Cretaceous of Spain." volume="35" year="2000">
Rasnitsyn and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Martínez-Delclòs">Martinez-Delclos</normalizedToken>
2000
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
